race.description: The Steel & Strength Roadrunner Maiden Plate
race.comment: ALASKA DREAM (1) tried hard but found a couple better last start over 1400m at Taree. Has only raced twice and looks ready to tackle this longer trip. Not a great deal of depth to this maiden so he gets his chance. PIERANT (6) is a 16-start maiden who was thoroughly outclassed in the $250k Magic Millions Maiden at the Gold Coast last time out. Beaten narrowly over 2000m at the end of last prep so getting out to this trip should spark some improvement. EXODINI (10) was lining up for only the second time when a closing fourth over 1400m at Gatton recently. Enjoys a soft run from the inside draw and this longer trip should be right in his wheelhouse. YIANNI (9) started favourite but finished last of four in a poor performance over 1512m at Port Macquarie last start. That followed a 32-day break so he should strip fitter for this. REDADEL (7) is next best on a seven-day back-up.
